Subject: Re: [T2] clutch cable?

On Mon, 16 Dec 2002 MrGarretsn(-at-)aol.com wrote:

> Hi, this morning I had trouble with my 72 bus.  I started the engine in 1st
> gear, and it jumped forward and stalled.  I then started in neutral and when
> I shifted into reverse, it jumped and stalled again.  The clutch pedal feels
> spongy and has less resistance than 2 days ago when everything worked fine.
> Does this sound like a clutch cable or something worse?  How do I know if the
> cable is bad?  I know that replacing a cable is supposed to be fairly easy
> and I think that I am ready to try it.  Can someone tell me the steps, or is
> this in the archives?
> Thanks in advance, Rob
> 72 Bus

It's probably a cable or a bad throwout fork.  Crawl under the back end
and try moving the operating lever by hand.  If it only moves a little, it
is a bad cable.  if it moves more than an quarter inch or so it is the
fork.

George
